<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-05-21T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-05-21T10:00:00-05:00" n="759" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d759">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123 G 861/298A: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the High Commissioner in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-05-21T11:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                        1927—11 a.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>49. Your 36, May 19, 10 a.m. Official announcement of Mr. Grew’s
                            appointment made last evening. You may confirm it.<note n="44" xml:id="d759fn44">Ambassador Grew presented his letter of credence
                                to the President of Turkey on October 12 (file No. 123 G
                                861/312).</note></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
